        <div n="060-04B1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-1"> Peruse my leaves through every part,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-2"> And think thou see'st my owner's heart,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-3"> Scrawl'd o'er with trifles thus, and quite</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-4"> As hard, as senseless, and as light;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-5"> Expos'd to every coxcomb's eyes,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-6"> But hid with caution from the wise.</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-7"> Here you may read──<hi rend="underline">dear charming saint</hi>,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-8"> Beneath──<hi rend="underline">a true receipt for paint</hi>:</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-9"> Here, in beau spelling──<hi rend="underline">tru tel deth</hi>;</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-10"> There, in her own──<hi rend="underline">far an el breth</hi>;</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-11"> Here──<hi rend="underline">lovely nymph, pronounce my doom</hi>:</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-12"> There──<hi rend="underline">a safe way to use perfume</hi>.</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-13"> Here a page fill'd with billet-doux;</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-14"> On t'other side──<hi rend="underline">laid out for shoes</hi>:</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-15"> Madam, I die without your grace;</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-16"> Item──<hi rend="underline">for half a yard of lace</hi>.</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-17"> Who that had wit would place it here</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-18"> For ev'ry peeping fop to jeer?<gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/></l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-19"> Whoe'er expects to hold his part</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-20"> In such a book and such a heart,</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-21"> If he be wealthy and a fool,</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-22"> Is in all points the fittest tool;</l><l n="23" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-23"> Of whom it may be justly said,</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-060-04B1-line-24"> He's a gold pencil tipp'd with lead.060-04B1   </l></lg></div>
